An Italian Easter Awaits ( https://resy.com/cities/washington-dc/venues/lar=
dente?date=3D2026-03-31&seats=3D2 )
***************************************************************************=
*******************************

Celebrate Easter the Italian way at L'Ardente, where indulgence is always o=
n the menu. The star of the holiday is our Berkshire porcelet porchetta, ru=
bbed with Calabrian chilies, orange zest, fennel and other spices before hi=
tting the oven. It's served over creamy Parmesan polenta with a touch of es=
pelette, alongside roasted carrots, Granny Smith apples, and a bright agrod=
olce sauce that brings balance to every bite.

=E2=80=8B

Our new brunch brings both the full dinner menu=E2=80=94yes, including our =
iconic lasagna=E2=80=94all day alongside a brunch menu that runs through 3:=
45 p.m. every Saturday and Sunday. So gather with friends, celebrate with f=
amily, and settle in for a day that blends brunch ease with dinner-worthy d=
ecadence.

=E2=80=8B

And if you miss out on the Easter Sunday special, the porchetta will also b=
e available for dinner service on Monday. Reservations are encouraged for w=
hat promises to be a beautifully bustling holiday.

